BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 4906.011 of the Revised Code be 3
enacted to read as follows: 4
Sec. 4906.011. (A) As used in this section : 5
(1)(a) "Affordable energy source" means an energy resource 6
that meets all of the following criteria: 7
(i) Has a stable and predictable cost; 8
(ii) Provides a cost-effective means of heating, cooling, 9
and generating electricity; 10
(iii) Delivers substantial savings related to residential 11
and commercial customers comparable to energy sources listed in 12
42 U.S.C. 15852(b), based on the average cost per unit of energy 13
output calculated to include any direct or indirect payment by 14
any level of government for the previous five years; 15
(b) "Affordable energy source" does not include advanced 16
nuclear energy technology. 17

