(2) "Advanced nuclear energy technology" means generation 18
III technology as defined by the nuclear regulatory commission; 19
other, later technology; or significant improvements to existing 20
facilities. 21
(3) "Reliable energy source" means an energy resource that 22
meets both of the following criteria: 23
(a) Is readily available at all times to meet energy 24
demands with minimal interruptions during high-usage periods; 25
(b) When used for power generation, the resource 26
demonstrates all of the following: 27
(i) A minimum capacity factor of fifty per cent; 28
(ii) Electricity output that is dispatchable at all times 29
and with the capability to ramp up or down electricity 30
generation within one hour to stabilize the electrical grid; 31
(iii) The ability to complement and provide backup to 32
renewable energy resources during periods of low availability. 33
(4)(a) "Clean energy source" means any energy generated by 34
utilizing those sources listed in 42 U.S.C. 15852(b) or 35
hydrocarbons, which, when combusted for the purpose of 36
electricity generation, meet the national ambient air quality 37
standards set by the United States environmental protection 38
agency under the authority of the "Clean Air Act," 42 U.S.C. 39
7401 et seq. 40
(b) "Clean energy source" includes: 41
(i) Energy generated by nuclear reaction; 42
(ii) Energy generated using natural gas. 43
(5) "Domestic production" means a fuel source that is 44

