primarily produced within the United States. 45
(6) "Infrastructure security" means infrastructure 46
necessary to deliver energy to customers that minimizes reliance 47
on foreign nations for critical materials or manufacturing. 48
(7) "Foreign adversary nation" means any country specified 49
in 10 U.S.C. 4872(f)(2). 50
(B) It is declared to be the public policy of the state, 51
in order to ensure affordable, reliable, and clean energy 52
security within the state, to do the following in all cases 53
involving an application for a utility facility certificate 54
under section 4906.06 of the Revised Code: 55
(1) Employ affordable, reliable, and clean energy sources; 56
(2) Ensure that, except for energy generated by nuclear 57
reaction, the state prioritizes domestic production; 58
(3) Minimize reliance on foreign adversary nations for 59
critical materials or manufacturing by prioritizing 60
infrastructure necessary to deliver energy to Ohio customers. 61

